item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

It is more a surprise that the hp calculation have been inside all the time. Cause you have to send 2 int values for every entity. That makes it on a busy world about 10000 useless ints every person. Just see the profit if you do all those silly calculation at the server.

This is no way intended to break an updater. To be more specific, if we had bce bots at the time of aryan. There would be 80% less broken in the engine update. The only thing they killed is deobs and action forcing. (Unless your a great programmer and have time to get around those protections). If you rename current clients with a old deob, you can find almost anything back. Only Interface has changed dramaticly.

Read full topic
